article.headline: UAB 69, Southern Miss 65
article.story: HATTIESBURG, Miss. (AP) -- Gabe Kennedy scored 16 points and UAB was 7-for-9 from the free throw line in the final 3{ minutes to thwart a rally by Southern Mississippi and come away with a 69-65 victory on Wednesday night. UAB led by as many as seven in the second half, but Southern Miss (11-9, 4-5 Conference USA) tied the game at 58 with 3:35 to play on two free throws by Jasper Johnson. The Blazers responded with a dunk off a turnover by Demario Eddins and some steady shooting from the line down the stretch to clinch their fifth win in six games. Kennedy was 6-for-11 from the field and Eddins scored 15 points for the Blazers (14-6, 7-2 Conference USA), who shot nearly 52 percent in the second half. UAB made just two second half turnovers, after committing nine in the first half. Jarekus Singleton scored a career-high 21 points on 7-for-10 shooting for Southern Miss. Charles Gaines added 20 points, 12 in the first half, and eight rebounds for the Golden Eagles, who had won two straight. The Blazers opened the second half on an 8-2 run to take a 39-38. UAB opened its biggest lead of the game, 50-43, with 11:23 remaining on back-to-back 3-pointers from Ronell Taylor. Southern Miss used an 11-2 run in the first half to grab a seven-point lead with 6:40 to play. The Golden Eagles led 30-27 at the half.
